SOURCELINE function

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| SOURCELINE([line-number])                                                   |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Returns the text of the specified source program line, or the number of lines
if the line-number is omitted.  If source code is not available, a null string
is returned.

Examples:

	SOURCELINE()  == 10
	SOURCELINE(1) == '/* A 10-line program */'
